<paragraph id="8BAD36F3FFFAFFDEAECFFB28FFA0FA69" blockId="14.[189,1180,1235,1535]" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">
Compared with the small yellow species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEAC02FB2FFFD6FB7D" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1941" box="[624,743,1235,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="titschacki">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAC02FB2FFFD6FB7D" box="[624,743,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. titschacki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEAD54FB2FFE41FB7D" authorityName="Irmler" authorityYear="2012" box="[806,880,1235,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adisi">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAD54FB2FFE41FB7D" box="[806,880,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. adisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEADF2FB2FFEFFFB7D" authorityName="Irmler" authorityYear="2012" box="[896,974,1235,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pecki">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEADF2FB2FFEFFFB7D" box="[896,974,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. pecki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily to identify by the extremely small eyes. The species is as small as 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEAC87FB08FE5CFA9C" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1941" box="[757,877,1266,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="titschacki">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAC87FB08FE5CFA9C" box="[757,877,1266,1290]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. titschacki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and both species are slightly smaller than 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEAF31FAEAFCBCFABF" authorityName="Irmler" authorityYear="2012" box="[323,397,1297,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adisi">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAF31FAEAFCBCFABF" box="[323,397,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. adisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Antennae are slightly shorter than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEAD6EFAEAFEA2FABF" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1941" box="[796,915,1297,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="titschacki">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAD6EFAEAFEA2FABF" box="[796,915,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. titschacki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEADCDFAEAF906FABF" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1941" box="[959,1079,1297,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="titschacki">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEADCDFAEAF906FABF" box="[959,1079,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. titschacki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
antennae are as long as head and pronotum combined, whereas they are slightly shorter than pronotum in 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEAECFFAB4FC3AFAF0" authorityName="Irmler" authorityYear="2012" box="[189,267,1358,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pecki">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAECFFAB4FC3AFAF0" box="[189,267,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. pecki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEAFDBFAB4FCC9FAF0" authorityName="Irmler" authorityYear="2012" box="[425,504,1358,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pecki">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAFDBFAB4FCC9FAF0" box="[425,504,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. pecki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEAC5CFAB4FF97FAF0" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1941" box="[558,678,1358,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="titschacki">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAC5CFAB4FF97FAF0" box="[558,678,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. titschacki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEADBFFAB4F926FAF0" authorityName="Irmler" authorityYear="2012" box="[973,1047,1358,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adisi">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEADBFFAB4F926FAF0" box="[973,1047,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. adisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of two deep impressions on the pronotum, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEAC8CFA96FE79FA13" authorityName="Irmler" authorityYear="2012" box="[766,840,1389,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adisi">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAC8CFA96FE79FA13" box="[766,840,1389,1413]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. adisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has no impression on pronotum. 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEAECFFA77FC68FA35" box="[189,345,1419,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venezuelanus">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAECFFA77FC68FA35" box="[189,345,1419,1443]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. venezuelanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that is also similar to these three species is slightly darker. In males, the deep emargination of abdominal tergite VIII resembles that in 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEACA1FA50FE08FA54" authorityName="Irmler" authorityYear="2012" box="[723,825,1450,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEACA1FA50FE08FA54" box="[723,825,1450,1474]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEAD1CFA50FEE5FA54" authorityName="Irmler" authorityYear="2012" box="[878,980,1450,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAD1CFA50FEE5FA54" box="[878,980,1450,1474]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">E. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much larger, and punctation of tergite VIII is denser. Furthermore, the semicircular large apical plates of paramera are unique in the Neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D70FFFAFFDEAF81FA13FFA0FA69" box="[499,657,1511,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAF81FA13FF0CFA69" box="[499,573,1512,1535]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">Espeson</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3086578FFFAFFDFAECFF9E7FE35FC19" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="346" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAD36F3FFFAFFDEAECFF9E7FC71F9A2" blockId="14.[189,320,1564,1588]" box="[189,320,1564,1588]" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAECFF9E7FC71F9A2" bold="true" box="[189,320,1564,1588]" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">Description:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD36F3FFFAFFDFAECFF9B8FE8BFED4" blockId="14.[189,518,1603,1627]" lastBlockId="15.[106,1096,175,452]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="346" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAECFF9B8FC30F9CD" box="[189,257,1603,1627]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">Length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity id="4CEA9B16FFFAFFDEAF7CF9B8FC52F9CC" box="[270,355,1603,1627]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="14" pageNumber="345" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFAFFDEAF1FF9B8FC80F9CD" box="[365,433,1603,1627]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="345">Colour</emphasis>
: yellow. 
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFBFFDFAE18FF54FDAEFF51" box="[106,159,175,199]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">Head</emphasis>
: 
<quantity id="4CEA9B16FFFBFFDFAEC3FF54FC21FF51" box="[177,272,175,199]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="346" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.20 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CEA9B16FFFBFFDFAF29FF54FC8AFF51" box="[347,443,175,199]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="346" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
wide; eyes extremely small; only four or five ocellae; nearly invisible in dorsal aspect; temples twice as long as eyes and convexly prominent; fore-head straightly narrowed to more or less acute front edge of clypeus; setiferous punctation moderately dense and fine; on clypeus finer and denser than on lateral part of vertex; disc with impunctate midline; surface shiny; laterad with remains of weak microsculpture; disc polished.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD36F3FFFBFFDFAE18FEABFFD4FE52" blockId="15.[106,1096,175,452]" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFBFFDFAE18FEABFDF6FEF1" box="[106,199,336,359]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">Antennae</emphasis>
nearly as long as head and pronotum combined; 1 
<superScript id="7C679BBBFFFBFFDFAC93FEB4FFDAFECB" attach="left" box="[737,747,335,349]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">st</superScript>
and 2 
<superScript id="7C679BBBFFFBFFDFAD5DFEB5FE0EFECA" attach="left" box="[815,831,334,348]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">nd</superScript>
antennomere oblong, 3 
<superScript id="7C679BBBFFFBFFDFAA49FEB5F979FECA" attach="none" box="[1083,1096,334,348]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">rd</superScript>
conical; antennomeres 1 to 3 nearly equal in length; antennomere 4 and 5 more or less quadrate; following antennomeres wider than long; 8 
<superScript id="7C679BBBFFFBFFDFAC5FFE77FF0BFE0C" attach="left" box="[557,570,396,410]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">th</superScript>
antennomere narrower and smaller than antennomeres 7 and 9; 10 
<superScript id="7C679BBBFFFBFFDFAF50FE51FC1EFE2E" attach="left" box="[290,303,426,440]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">th</superScript>
antennomere nearly twice as wide as long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD36F3FFFBFFDFAE18FE28FDF9FD15" blockId="15.[106,1096,466,643]" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFBFFDFAE18FE28FDFDFE7C" box="[106,204,467,490]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">Pronotum</emphasis>
: 
<quantity id="4CEA9B16FFFBFFDFAEABFE29FC08FE7C" box="[217,313,466,490]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="346" unit="mm" value="0.23">0.23 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CEA9B16FFFBFFDFAF08FE29FCE8FE7C" box="[378,473,466,490]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="15" pageNumber="346" unit="mm" value="0.27">0.27 mm</quantity>
wide; with weak lateral margin; only visible in posterior half in dorsal aspect; deeply emarginate in posterior half; posterior edge only half as wide as width in anterior half; setiferous punctation deeper and coarser than on head; distance between punctures on average only half as wide as diameter of punctures; in anterior and posterior half each a small, but deep impression; surface shiny; laterad with remains of microsculpture, but surface mostly polished.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD36F3FFFBFFDFAE18FD69FEEBFD5E" blockId="15.[106,1096,658,712]" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFBFFDFAE18FD69FD94FD3C" box="[106,165,658,682]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">Elytra</emphasis>
: 
<quantity id="4CEA9B16FFFBFFDFAEC3FD69FC21FD3F" box="[177,272,658,682]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="15" pageNumber="346" unit="mm" value="0.26">0.26 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CEA9B16FFFBFFDFAF22FD69FC81FD3F" box="[336,432,658,682]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="346" unit="mm" value="0.33">0.33 mm</quantity>
wide; with setiferous punctation slightly weaker and sparser than on pronotum; with remains of microsculpture, but surface mostly polished and shiny.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD36F3FFFBFFDFAE18FD2CFD8DFCDD" blockId="15.[106,1096,727,843]" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFBFFDFAE18FD2CFDF8FD79" box="[106,201,727,751]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">Abdomen</emphasis>
with coarser punctation on anterior segments than on distal segments; microsculpture slightly more distinct than on elytra and, thus, surface less shiny; tergite VIII of male deeply emarginate in middle and with long acute teeth at outer angles; sparsely punctate also at lateral margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD36F3FFFBFFDFAE18FCA2FE35FC19" blockId="15.[106,1096,857,911]" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFBFFDFAE18FCA2FDF2FCE7" box="[106,195,857,881]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">Aedeagus</emphasis>
with long and thick basal part; apical part more or less straight and only half as long as basal part; paramera with large apical plate of semicircular shape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3086578FFFBFFDFAE18FC52FF4AFC71" pageId="15" pageNumber="346" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BAD36F3FFFBFFDFAE18FC52FDD2FC57" blockId="15.[106,227,937,961]" box="[106,227,937,961]" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis id="B966EAE1FFFBFFDFAE18FC52FDD2FC57" bold="true" box="[106,227,937,961]" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">Etymology:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD36F3FFFBFFDFAE18FC34FF4AFC71" blockId="15.[106,635,975,999]" box="[106,635,975,999]" pageId="15" pageNumber="346">The specific name refers to its collector James Peck.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
